Distribution (
Fig. 62
).
Pierella chalybaea
is distributed in Brazilian and Chacoan sub-regions, from Colombia to Bolivia (
Constantino 1995
;
Willmott et al 2011
;
Willmott & Hall 2014
;
Petit 2014
) and North and Midwest Brazil (Roraima, Amazonas, Pará, Acre, Rondônia, Mato Grosso and Goiás), apparently associated with both low altitudinal regions ( 100–900 m ) (
Brown 1948
) and high rainfall levels between 2000–5000 mm /year (Brown & Ab’Saber 1979 ).
